oc:kn_0f8a81ca a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When calling MCP tools that support filtering or bulk operations" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Avoid making many individual MCP tool calls in a loop when a single batched query with filters can retrieve all needed data. Use batching, caching, and parallel calls instead." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Individual calls in a loop cause severe performance degradation and may hit rate limits" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_1aac86ff a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:RecoveryTactic ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When troubleshooting MCP tool call failures" ;
    oc:directiveContent "When MCP tool calls fail, check: MCP server is configured and connected (via /mcp), authentication is valid, parameters match the tool schema exactly, and tool names are case-sensitive. Restart Claude Code after config changes." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Most MCP failures stem from misconfiguration, auth issues, or naming mismatches" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_77026adb a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When referencing any MCP tool in commands or agents" ;
    oc:directiveContent "MCP tool names follow the format: mcp__plugin_<plugin-name>_<server-name>__<tool-name>. Tool names are case-sensitive and must match exactly." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Incorrect tool names cause silent failures; the naming convention ensures tools are uniquely identified across plugins and servers" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_9f24c7a3 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building commands that call MCP tools" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Always validate required parameters before calling MCP tools, provide user feedback during long operations, format error messages with actionable remediation steps (not raw error codes), and document which MCP tools a command uses." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Good UX and error handling prevent user confusion and support issues" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_b42471a0 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing command frontmatter for MCP tool access" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Commands must pre-allow specific MCP tools in frontmatter using allowed-tools. Wildcards (mcp__plugin_<name>_<server>__*) should only be used when the command truly needs access to all tools from a server." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Pre-allowing limits the blast radius of a command and ensures only necessary tools are exposed" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_b4fee769 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing agents that use MCP tools" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Agents have broader tool access than commands — they can use any tool Claude determines necessary without pre-allowed lists. Agents should document which tools they typically use but don't need explicit frontmatter allowlists." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Agents are autonomous and need flexibility; commands are user-triggered and need tighter scoping" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_df380f27 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing command or agent workflows with MCP tools" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use four core tool call patterns: (1) Simple — single call with validation, (2) Sequential — chain dependent calls, (3) Batch — multiple calls with same tool, (4) Error-handling — try/retry with max attempts and graceful degradation." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Structured patterns reduce errors and make tool integrations more robust and maintainable" .

